<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        CAB DOOR AND HINGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAB DOOR AND HINGE</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600543">Figure 43</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600543" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600535.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Cab Door Check Strap</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RETAINING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHECK STRAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER DOOR COVER PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE MOUNTING BOLT 180 IN-LBS. (20 NM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ELECTRICAL CABLE (COURTESY LIGHT OR HEATED MIRRORS)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a sling or padded chain through the top of the window opening and attach sling to an
                    overhead hoist to support the door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the door has electrically controlled windows, heated mirrors, courtesy light or CB antenna,
                        disconnect the wiring to remove the door.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws (Item 1) securing door check strap (Item 2) to lower door cover panel
                    (Item 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Scribe the position of door hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600544">Item 34, Figure 44</hotlnk>) at upper and lower corners of hinge on the
                    door. This will help when re-installing the door.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600544" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600536.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 44. Cab Door Window and Vent Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. DOOR VENT WINDOW</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. WINDOW OPENING SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. GLASS RUN CHANNEL RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. DOOR GLASS</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. GLASS RUN CHANNEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. GLASS SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. SIDE DOOR LOCK FILLER</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. DOOR GLASS CHANNEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. REGULATOR ARM RETAINING CLIP</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. LOCK CONTROL KNOB</callout1>
                        <callout1>11. LOCK CONTROL ROD BUSHING</callout1>
                        <callout1>12. INNER LOCK CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>13. UPPER LOCK CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>14. LOCK ROD RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>15. DOOR LOCK ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>16. DOOR LATCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>17. LOCK OUTER CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>18. LOCK CYLINDER CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>19. REGULATOR HANDLE WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>20. WINDOW REGULATOR HANDLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>21. WINDOW CRANK SOCKET HEAD SCREW</callout1>
                        <callout1>22. MANIFEST POCKET (STANDARD ON ECONOMY TRIM)</callout1>
                        <callout1>23. GRAB HANDLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>24. ARM REST (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                        <callout1>25. INNER DOOR PULL HANDLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>26. INNER (REMOTE) HANDLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>27. UPPER DOOR COVER PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>28. WINDOW REGULATOR ARM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>29. WINDOW STOP BUMPER</callout1>
                        <callout1>30. OUTER HANDLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>31. REAR GLASS CHANNEL RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>32. LEFT CHANNEL RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>33. DOOR CHECK STRAP ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>34. DOOR HINGE</callout1>
                        <callout1>35. VIEW GLASS SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>36. RIGHT DOOR VIEW GLASS</callout1>
                        <callout1>37. LOWER DOOR COVER PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>38. ASH RECEPTACLE (RIGHT DOOR ONLY)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts (Item 4) securing door to door hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600544">Item 34, Figure 44</hotlnk>), and remove door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move door to a work bench or other support as required. Cover bench with a material that
                    will not scratch painted surfaces of the door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove cab door hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600544">Item 34, Figure 44</hotlnk>), scribe position of door hinge on hinge
                    pillar at upper and lower corners of hinge. This will help when re-installing hinge to hinge pillar.
                    Then remove bolts securing it to the cab.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the door hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600544">Item 34, Figure 44</hotlnk>) was removed from the cab, position the door
                    hinge on the cab. Align the hinge with the scribe marks on the hinge pillar and secure it with the
                    bolts. Tighten to 180 in-lbs. (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the door on the overhead support.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the door in position and install the hinge bolts (Item 4) securing it to the door
                    hinge. Align the hinge with the scribe marks on the door and tighten the hinge bolts to 180 in-lbs.
                    (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the door has electrically controlled windows, heated mirrors, courtesy light or CB antenna,
                        reconnect the wiring.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To align the door to the door opening, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16005v_76.xml" xrefid="x1600506">ADJUSTMENTS, CAB DOOR HINGE
                        <xref refid="x1600506"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the door check strap (Item 2) on the lower door cover panel (Item 3) and install
                    the retaining screws (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
